Live Response Collection on Windows & Linux Endpoints
Learning Objectives
By completing this lab, you will:

Perform live response data collection on Windows and Linux systems
Use open-source tools for incident response and forensic analysis
Compare and analyze collected data from different operating systems
Understand key artifacts and evidence sources in live response scenarios
Prerequisites
Basic understanding of Linux command line operations
Familiarity with file systems and process management
Knowledge of network concepts and system administration
Understanding of incident response fundamentals
Lab Environment
Al Nafi provides Linux-based cloud machines for this lab. Simply click Start Lab to access your dedicated environment. The provided Linux machine is bare metal with no pre-installed tools, so you will install all required tools during the lab exercises.

Task 1: Collect Live Data from a Windows Endpoint
Subtask 1.1: Set Up Windows Environment and Tools
Install QEMU and create a Windows environment:

# Update system and install required packages
sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade -y
sudo apt install -y qemu-kvm qemu-utils virtinst virt-manager libvirt-daemon-system libvirt-clients bridge-utils

# Download Windows 10 evaluation ISO (replace with current link)
wget -O windows10.iso "https://software-download.microsoft.com/download/pr/19041.508.200927-1902.20h2_release_svc_refresh_CLIENTENTERPRISEEVAL_OEMRET_x64FRE_en-us.iso"

# Create virtual disk
qemu-img create -f qcow2 windows10.qcow2 40G

# Start Windows VM (run in background)
qemu-system-x86_64 -enable-kvm -m 4096 -cpu host -smp 2 -drive file=windows10.qcow2,format=qcow2 -cdrom windows10.iso -boot d -vnc :1 &
